Description: Fragment of flattened handle from neck join to sharpish turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine buff. Rectangular stamp with rose(?) symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Menestratos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0385.32.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (185)
